Our personal experience allows us to say that limits are only in our mind and not in our physical condition. 3pi mobility came up out of a latent need for movement, integration and autonomy for those of us who use a wheelchair, focusing on a space that has not yet been explored by the Argentinian industry. We foster a change of perception, not only by our users but also by those who are not disabled, generating an integrative revolution. We seek to make a difference from the practicality, technology and quality of our products, allowing those who use them to lead a healthy and outdoor life. Toruk has two hooks that connect to the wheelchair on both sides, causing the two front wheels to rise making both parts end up becoming a tricycle. It is propelled with both hands and the weight of the head and body are used for propulsion. It can be attached to every wheelchair, it decreases the risk of falling due to wells and sidewalks, something very frequent in Argentina, and it helps to improve the aerobic capacity of its users. Toruk's propulsion, unlike the movement required by the wheelchair, does not harm the arms.

Pactanda is unbiased and company friendly generating loyalty and opportunities for up- and cross-selling for "good" companies. First Contact 3D is the first way to bring ultrasound techniques into the real 3D world.
